.TH "of_dma_get_range" 9 "of_dma_get_range" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
of_dma_get_range \- Get DMA range info and put it into a map array
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" of_dma_get_range
.BI "(struct device_node *np "  ","
.BI "const struct bus_dma_region **map "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "np" 12
device node to get DMA range info
.IP "map" 12
dma range structure to return
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Look in bottom up direction for the first "dma-ranges" property
and parse it.  Put the information into a DMA offset map array.

dma-ranges format:
DMA addr (dma_addr)     : naddr cells
CPU addr (phys_addr_t)  : pna cells
size                    : nsize cells

It returns -ENODEV if "dma-ranges" property was not found for this
device in the DT.
